The paper deals with error correction codes and their performance over channels, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The use of concatenated codes and their encoding/decoding complexity suggests that it could also belong to the Coding Theory and Cryptography (cs.CC) category. The mention of memoryless channels and the revision to Forney's decoding algorithm suggests that it could belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) category. The use of concatenated codes and their performance over channels also suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) category. Finally, the mention of low complexity integration suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category.
